{"id":67010,"date":"2022-11-28T05:02:15","date_gmt":"2022-11-28T10:02:15","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/?p=67010"},"modified":"2022-11-21T09:30:27","modified_gmt":"2022-11-21T14:30:27","slug":"10-crazy-ways-weve-saved-money-over-the-years","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/10-crazy-ways-weve-saved-money-over-the-years\/","title":{"rendered":"10 Crazy Ways We&#8217;ve Saved Money Over The Years"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><strong>Morning!!<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>Back with some more great ways to save them dollars! Courtesy of <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/reel\/ClCkhcSApNf\/?igshid=MTI5NDc2ZGU=\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">The Debt Free Guys<\/a> today which I stole yet again off Instagram, lol&#8230;<\/p>\n<p>THERE&#8217;S JUST SO MANY GREAT VIDEOS THERE from our community!!\u00a0 And much faster\/fun to digest too &#8211; I feel like a dinosaur still just blogging away my thoughts here &#x1f602;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Anyways, see which ones you can adapt to your own life!<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>And hopefully it at least includes the first one (hubba hubba)&#8230;<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">******<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/p\/ClCkhcSApNf\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-67014\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta.png\" alt=\"crazy ways save money\" width=\"387\" height=\"683\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta.png 626w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta-170x300.png 170w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta-581x1024.png 581w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta-550x970.png 550w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta-284x500.png 284w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/crazy-ways-save-money-insta-612x1080.png 612w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 387px) 100vw, 387px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>[Click <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/p\/ClCkhcSApNf\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">the video<\/a> to watch it on Insta (the dancing is spectacular! ;)), or peruse below for their write up + my two cents&#8230; If it reads weird it&#8217;s because it was shortened for Instagram.]<\/em><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">******<\/p>\n<p>We\u2019re always looking for ways to cut expenses so we can put the extra into investing to build cash flow.<\/p>\n<h3 style=\"text-align: center;\">Here are 10 crazy ways we\u2019ve saved money over the years:<\/h3>\n<p><strong>#1. Naked Sundays in the summer.<\/strong> Stay home vs. spend on expensive brunches and entertainment. Stock up on food and drinks, plan fun things to do. [Reminds me of <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/introducing-strip-budgeting\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">strip budgeting<\/a>, lol&#8230; everything is more fun without clothes on!]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#2. Do a dry month.<\/strong> Cut as much as $400 from spending (less likely to dine out). Opportunity to connect with sober friends. [YES! Plus it&#8217;s a great break for your <em>health<\/em> too and shows you can really accomplish hard things if you need to&#8230; I&#8217;m currently in week #4 without a sip of alcohol and it&#8217;s not as bad now that I&#8217;ve gotten past that first week of hell! Lol&#8230; (but will probably stop at the end of the month as I enjoy it too much :)]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#3. Keep our phones for 5+ years.<\/strong> $25 to $35\/month to rent = $1,500 to $2,100\/year. Put on rewards credit card to earn free travel. [I&#8217;m still an old school Android Galaxy user myself, going on 8 years now, and only paying <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/republic-wireless-review-cell-phone-savings\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">$30\/mo<\/a>&#8230; Sometimes I do need to shell out an extra $5 to bump up my bandwidth with all this new Instagram watching I&#8217;m doing, haha, but by and large it&#8217;s saved me thousands over the years and don&#8217;t have any plans on going back&#8230;)<\/p>\n<p><strong>#4. Choose a limited data plan.<\/strong> Use Wi-Fi instead. Saves $80\/month. [Yup, see note above!]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#5. Stick to the same simple menu and grocery list.<\/strong> Planning meals makes shopping easier. Splurge from time to time (keeps it special). [Agreed! Mrs. BudgetsAreSexy does most of our cooking\/shopping, but it&#8217;s usually the same core meals each week with one or two swapped around to keep it interesting&#8230; In fact, she just started writing out the week&#8217;s meals on a wipey board in our kitchen too so everyone knows what we&#8217;ll be having each day now. Which is great as it lessens the barrage of questions from our kids!]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#6. Grocery shop every 7 to 10 days.<\/strong> Less time in-store = less money spent. Build a menu around foods already at home or on sale. [I don&#8217;t think this is possible with a million kids, but yes &#8211; less trips is preferable :)]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#7. Semi-annual spending analysis.<\/strong> Opens eyes to unconscious spending\/budget creep. Reminds us of goals and keeps us on track. [And if you really want to impress the pants off your significant other, put together a <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/a-financial-powerpoint-presentation-that-screams-i-love-you\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">nerdy powerpoint<\/a> on everything!]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#8. Make our own iced coffee daily in the summer.<\/strong> Up to $12 for iced coffee x 4 visits\/week = $3K\/year. Save by using a French press, storing in reused spaghetti jars. [Not here, lol&#8230; I do make my first cup of coffee at home while I&#8217;m doing &#8220;me&#8221; time in the mornings, but once the kids are out the door IT&#8217;S COFFEE SHOP TIME FOR ME!!!! Mainly for the ambiance and people and easier motivation to work though vs the coffee itself as it basically doubles as my &#8220;office space&#8221;. (And is significantly cheaper &#8211; just costs a cup of coffee!)]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#9. Bought\/rented housing with 1 salary.<\/strong> Doesn\u2019t mean can\u2019t have a beautiful home. Allowed us to put away hundreds of thousands of $ in 401(k)s. [Yes yes yes! Living off 50% of your income does wonders for your flexibility and goals&#8230; You could even take it as far as stopping work altogether if you wanted to and just coast right into <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/wifefi-status-activated\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WifeFI<\/a>! ;)]<\/p>\n<p><strong>#10. Drove a 2006 MINI Cooper for 15 years.<\/strong> $100\/month car maintenance vs. $500\/month car payment. Saved $50K (including the $8K spent on maintenance). [Makes me miss Frankencaddy so bad, ugh&#8230; No monthly payments is nice, but it&#8217;s even better when your car actually <a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/franken-caddy-car-keeps-making-money\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MAKES you money<\/a> &#8211; heyo!!!]<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/franken-caddy-car-keeps-making-money\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-50991 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/frankencaddy.jpg\" alt=\"frankencaddy\" width=\"550\" height=\"386\" srcset=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/frankencaddy.jpg 550w, https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/images\/frankencaddy-300x211.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">******<\/p>\n<p><em><strong>How about you? What funky tricks are you doing lately that saves you some green??<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re on Insta, let me know so I can stalk your life too! ;)<\/p>\n<p>You can find me <a href=\"https:\/\/www.instagram.com\/jmoneyyyyyy\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">@jmoneyyyyyy<\/a>.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Morning!! Back with some more great ways to save them dollars! Courtesy of The Debt Free Guys today which I stole yet again off Instagram,&#8230; <\/p>\n<p class=\"more\"><a class=\"more-link\" href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/10-crazy-ways-weve-saved-money-over-the-years\/\">Read More<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":3,"featured_media":67015,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[12],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-67010","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-saving"],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO Premium plugin v24.6 (Yoast SEO v24.5) - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>10 Crazy Ways We&#039;ve Saved Money Over The Years<\/title>\n<meta name=\"description\" content=\"A bunch of tips on how to save money! From cutting down cell phone bills to simple menu making to my new favorite day - NAKED SUNDAYS!!\" \/>\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"index, follow, max-snippet:-1, max-image-preview:large, max-video-preview:-1\" \/>\n<link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/10-crazy-ways-weve-saved-money-over-the-years\/\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:locale\" content=\"en_US\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"10 Crazy Ways We&#039;ve Saved Money Over The Years\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"A bunch of tips on how to save money! From cutting down cell phone bills to simple menu making to my new favorite day - NAKED SUNDAYS!!\" \/>\n<meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https:\/\/budgetsaresexy.vercel.app\/10-crazy-ways-weve-saved-money-over